<article id="post-103652" class="post-103652 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-uncategorized">
	<div class="article-header">
		
				
		<h1 class="article-title">Inside the story of one Mexican restaurateur&#8217;s journey to success in the South Bronx</h1>
		
		
		
						<div class="article-meta">
				
				<span class="byline"><img alt='' src='https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Bx-homescreen-2.png' srcset='https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Bx-homescreen-2.png 2x' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' decoding='async'/><span class="name">By <a href="https://www.bxtimes.com/author/et-rodriguez/" title="Posts by ET Rodriguez" class="author url fn" rel="author">ET Rodriguez</a></span></span>
				
				<span class="posted-on"><span class="intro">Posted on </span><a href="https://www.bxtimes.com/mexican-restaurateur-south-bronx/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2024-05-05T07:00:55-04:00">May 5, 2024</time></a></span>				
			</div><!-- .article-meta -->
				</div><!-- .article-header -->


	<div class="post-thumbnail">
	<div class="image-wrapper">
				
				<img width="1200" height="877" src="https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?w=1200" class="crop-center wp-post-image" alt="cantina tarasca" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg 2768w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=700,512 700w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=768,562 768w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=1200,877 1200w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=1536,1123 1536w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=2048,1498 2048w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=384,281 384w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=900,658 900w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=1600,1170 1600w, https://www.bxtimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/cincodemayo_jose.jpg?resize=50,37 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" />			</div>
	<div class="image-caption">After decades of hard work and struggle, Jose De Marcos Garcia is the proud owner of the new Cantina Tarasca at 576 Southern Blvd. </div>	<div class="image-credit">Photo ET Rodriguez</div></div><!-- .post-thumbnail -->

	<div class="addthis_inline_share_toolbox"></div>



	<div class="article-content">
		
	<figure class="promo-oneliner newsletter"><span style="margin-right: .1rem; color: #ccc;"><i class="far fa-envelope" aria-hidden="true"></i></span> <span>Sign up for our <a href="/newsletter/?utm_source=bxtimes&amp;utm_medium=oneliner&amp;utm_campaign=amnysportsnewsletter" target="_blank">Bronx Times email newsletter</a> to get news, updates, and local insights delivered straight to your inbox!</span></figure>
<div class="addtoany_share_save_container addtoany_content addtoany_content_top"><div class="a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 addtoany_list" data-a2a-url="https://www.bxtimes.com/mexican-restaurateur-south-bronx/" data-a2a-title="Inside the story of one Mexican restaurateur’s journey to success in the South Bronx"><a class="a2a_button_facebook" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/facebook?linkurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bxtimes.com%2Fmexican-restaurateur-south-bronx%2F&amp;linkname=Inside%20the%20story%20of%20one%20Mexican%20restaurateur%E2%80%99s%20journey%20to%20success%20in%20the%20South%20Bronx" title="Facebook" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_twitter" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/twitter?linkurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bxtimes.com%2Fmexican-restaurateur-south-bronx%2F&amp;linkname=Inside%20the%20story%20of%20one%20Mexican%20restaurateur%E2%80%99s%20journey%20to%20success%20in%20the%20South%20Bronx" title="Twitter" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_email" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/email?linkurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bxtimes.com%2Fmexican-restaurateur-south-bronx%2F&amp;linkname=Inside%20the%20story%20of%20one%20Mexican%20restaurateur%E2%80%99s%20journey%20to%20success%20in%20the%20South%20Bronx" title="Email" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_dd addtoany_share_save addtoany_share" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share"></a></div></div><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It&#8217;s Cinco de Mayo for the 163rd time, marking the anniversary of Mexico’s win against the French in the battle of Puebla in 1862. And while you partake in the celebrations, leave your sombreros and sarapes at home and instead, pay homage to the arduous plight so many Mexicans faced to bring you your chips and margaritas.</span></p><div class='s2nPlayer k-9FQ6NFAV' data-type='float'></div><script type='text/javascript' src='//embed.sendtonews.com/player3/embedcode.js?fk=9FQ6NFAV&cid=14023&offsetx=100&offsety=0&floatwidth=400&floatposition=bottom-right' data-type='s2nScript'></script>

<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">“I came out of work on a Friday, I’m almost home and then he hit me and said ‘give me the f&#8212;&#8212; money’,” said Jose De Marcos Garcia, owner of Cantina Tarasca on Southern Boulevard in the South Bronx. </span></p><div id="emp-b7db2" class="emp-ad-article-leaderboard" style="text-align:center;"><script type="text/javascript">if (!window.AdButler){(function(){var s = document.createElement("script"); s.async = true; s.type = "text/javascript";s.src = 'https://ads.empowerlocal.co/app.js';var n = document.getElementsByTagName("script")[0]; n.parentNode.insertBefore(s, n);}());}</script>
                <script type="text/javascript">
